cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper presents a data-based policy for iterative control tasks, which involves constructing a piecewise affine approximation to the value function using input and state trajectories. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Control Systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a user-defined cost function, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The experiments are carried out on the Berkeley Autonomous Race Car (BARC) platform, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of value functions and linear programming suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
